Rare contemporary 3 bed, 3 full bath (or 2 bed + den/office) with PRIVATE ENTRANCE. Townhouse style condo on 2 levels w/private entrance offers home-like feel but w/luxury amenities. Renovated features include Viking appliances, custom Tech Lighting, stone & glass tile throughout, custom closets, luxury custom drapes, partial motorized shades, high ceilings w/floor to ceiling windows, contemporary lighting, hardwood floors, 1 parking space. Across from Oracle Park & oceanfront, private entrance w/patio viewing ballpark allows access from street + great for entertaining friends & family during baseball season or world-famous concerts & events at Oracle Park. Deluxe amenities: 24 hr concierge, valet parking, heated outdoor pool & spa, BBQ & fireplace, sauna, electric charging, entertainment room, business center, conference room, Fitness Center w/views, Brixton Restaurant. Steps from Caltrain, Muni, Safeway, 15 min walk to Ferry Building, BART, Chase Center, easy highway access

Located just a couple of blocks away from the heart of the Inner Sunset, one of the most coveted dining & shopping corridors in The City. Beautifully retained 1925 Spanish Med. detail in this terrific 3br/2ba home of 1550 SQFT per tax records. Gorgeous hardwood floors in most areas of the home. Wood trim and original built-ins, wood burning fireplace and coved ceilings will blow your mind. All bedrooms & bathrooms are permitted. Sun room off of the kitchen legality is not known. Enjoy all of the dining options, including Ebisu, Nopalito, Arizmendi Bakery & San Tung. Numerous local boutiques line 9th ave and Irving St. Just a couple of blocks to GG Park, the arboretum, botanical gardens & The De Young Museum. Whether you commute by bicycle or the numerous public transportation options or need access to 280 to the Peninsula, 80 to the East Bay or 101 to Marin, the location could not be more convenient. What a great home for the price of a condo in the best of locations. Welcome home!

Sophisticated living meets high tech sensibility in this rarely available urban loft !! Spacious 2 bedroom 2 full bath plus office space has plenty of room to work from home! Fall in love with the open concept design, light and bright interiors, soaring ceiling heights. Build in custom made shelves and cabinets in the office space and entry way. Commuters delight, easy access to Caltrain Station. The gorgeous courtyard with a water fountain can be rented out for private events. Assigned one car parking. Please note, the office space is not permitted and not included in sqft. This is quintessential San Francisco living at its best! Don't miss out!

Top-floor unit in Contemporary elevator building. This 2-bedroom and 2 full bath unit is in move-in condition with fresh paint & new carpet. Modern kitchen features electric stove/micro-wave/dish washer/refrigerator. Living/dining room combination. Patio deck. 1-car deeded parking. Both bedrooms face Golden Gate park. SAFEWAY is exactly 1 block away. Unit is squeaky clean. Laundry at corner of 7th/Balboa.

Fall in love with this beautiful home located in the desirable Mission District. Just steps away from James Rolph Playground and Potrero del Sol Community Garden, this beautifully remodeled home is everything you have been looking for! Flexible and easy-living floor plan offers 2 spacious bedrooms, cozy living room with new laminate flooring, remodeled kitchen and bathroom on the main level. Work from home? Extended family visits? Don't miss the downstairs in-law unit featuring one bedroom, full bathroom, kitchenette and living area that makes room for extended family, or can lease out for extra income! One off street parking spot, as well as one full car garage. Laundry closet on site. Good size backyard, great for entertaining. Don't miss out on this great opportunity!

address: 230 North Lake Merced Hls Unit 1D, San Francisco, CA 94132
description: Beautiful specious private resort-like condo in Lake Merced Hills. This lovely and bright home features custom cabinets. double paned Marvin windows, custom screen for some of the windows and sliding doors throughout the unit. This living room has stylish hardwood flooring, recessed lighting, and prewired speaker system. Both living room and dining area open onto an enclosed deck. Eat-in remodeled kitchen and brand-new washer and dryer. 3-spacious bedrooms, including a master bedroom with shower over tub and a walk-in closet. All bedrooms have access to the patio. There are 1-storage room ,1-designated parking space in garage, and plenty of guest parking. Complex amenities include 24-hour security, heated swimming pool, Jacuzzi/spa, 3 tennis courts, sauna, recently renovated recreation room, clubhouse with a fully equipped kitchen.Walking distance to Lake Merced and close to 4-golf courses, Stonestown Mall,grocery,restaurants,Lowell HS and SFSU, and Westlake Shopping, Hwy 280 and BART

340 Sanchez is a 2-bed, 1-bath, 1-car parking, 11-foot-ceiling, comfortable Victorian condominium with just the right mix of modern touches. With about 1100 sqft, 340 has charming elements like rich millwork, wood floors, a clawfoot tub + sparkling antique chandeliers alongside a deeded storage room, parking, a concrete foundation, an updated kitchen + easy outdoor access. Met by an elegant and inviting living room with a big bay window, 340's layout separates its bedrooms for a bit more privacy with one overlooking the lush back garden, which is just outside a combined kitchen/dining area. 340's kitchen updates include a new island gas cooktop, new stainless sink + faucet and, like the rest of 340, new functional + dramatic LED lighting. The kitchen also has a dishwasher, French-door refrigerator + full pantry. Despite its close proximity to so much, e.g., Dolores + Duboce Parks, the block still has a vibe of a neighborly sanctuary. Yes, 340 Sanchez is the home you're looking for.

Desirable well maintained two level house in the Parkside neighborhood with ocean view. Well set up with 2/2 upper level with a good size center light-well brings lot of natural light and breeze.Two large size bedrooms(one master set),breakfast room, separate dinning room are on the same floor! Hallway bathroom has both a shower and tub. Hardwood floor through out the house.Downstair permitted with 1bed/1bath plus a family room, all in move in condition. Large one car garage with plenty of storage space! Library, Shops, restaurants and MUNI "L"on Taraval Street just 2 short blocks away. One block up to Lincoln High School!

address: 54 Stanford Heights Ave, San Francisco, CA 94127
description: Charming mid-century modern home located in desirable Miraloma District with panoramic views of San Francisco. Move-in ready renovated kitchen Quartz waterfall countertop, shaker white wood cabinets, new stainless steel appliances and hardware. Bathrooms updated with Italian ceramic tiles with walk-in shower stalls. Main level features living, dining and kitchen view of SF. Evenings perfect for candle light dinner view of city lights. New garage door,opener and furnace. Easy access to Hwy 280,101, Glen Park Muni/BART and downtown SF. Nearby Sunnyside Playground, Miraloma Elementary, Mt.Davidson and Glen Canyon Parks and trails.

Reside comfortably in this inviting, top-level Owner's unit while collecting rental income from the occupied unit downstairs! Both 2 bed, 1 bath flats are identical in layout, and feature living room fireplaces and formal dining rooms. A useful chair lift services the interior-entry staircase to both units. The ground floor level features side-by-side parking, individual laundry, and expansive storage rooms. The back yard has both a sitting area and a planted garden for your enjoyment. Conveniently located across the street from shops, with grocery stores and restaurants nearby. MUNI bus lines 7 and 29 each stop a block away. Easy proximity to schools, Ocean Beach, and Golden Gate Park.

Upper Lapham Way is a very peaceful oasis, subject enjoys a stunning view of the bay and over looks the San Bruno Mountains. The Yard is ample with the opportunity to build a great spacious deck that will rock your soul. The morning sunrise will memorize your desire to start your day off great! It's best for you to see this hidden gem before it disappears. Subject is partially remodeled with its own unique character, but with a little elbow grease you can turn it into your very own home sweet home! Three Bedrooms, Two bath, Large living room with wood burning fire place. Exposed hardwood floor throughout, and to top it off a bonus bedroom with a full bath. Not guaranteed by Seller nor agents.

address: 1264 - B Golden Gate Ave, San Francisco, CA 94115
description: 3 BD/2 BA TIC located in the vibrant Fillmore District. This Victorian Unit has been refreshed and move in ready. Enjoy the light filled unit with 11 foot ceilings. The unit features a flexible living space, open kitchen, primary bedroom with bathroom ensuite, 2 additional bedrooms and additional bathroom. Great space for growing family or work from home. There is a combo washer/dryer, shared garage with 1 parking space, and storage locker. Convenient location with easy access to public transportation, freeways, shops, restaurants and walking distance to other neighborhoods such as Hayes Valley, Alamo Square, and Lower Pacific Heights.

Welcome to Residence #413 at Knox, an industrial-influenced, newly built development on the border of Dogpatch/Potrero. Ideally located within walking distance to the 22nd Caltrain Station & Third Street Muni line, this spacious split two bedroom unit offers beautiful views of a lush garden and plenty of natural light. The residence features a great open floorplan with large windows, quartz counters throughout, upgraded appliances including washer/dryer in unit and NEST air conditioning. Building amenities includes, a Fitness center, BBQ area, Media room, Package room, Bike room, Lobby attendant, & smart intercom entry. Additionally, Knox is considered one of the most sought after buildings in San Francisco, with phenomenal homeowners that will make any newcomer feel completely at home.

Located in the heart of the Parkside district, this radiant 2 bed/1 bath retreat offers visual resplendence and respite in the form of light-filled rooms, arched doorways, parquet hardwood floors, and an array of thoughtfully considered details to delight the senses. Parquet fl, medallion design at the foyer. a spacious living room adorning a charming fireplace with a decorative mantel, gorgeous crown molding, a tray ceiling, and windows graced with plantation shutters. The kitchen boasts a suite of stainless steel appliances and skylights for added luminosity while decorative tile work in the bathroom beckons you to enjoy calm and tranquility during all your daily rituals. a deck outside the kitchen in addition to a low maintenance backyard and having more space for plants provides the perfect setting. For added convenience, an in-unit washer/dryer and features a bonus family room and bath. Located near Golden Gate Park and restaurants. 20 mins from SF DT.

Wonderful Outer Sunset home perfect for first time buyers and those wishing to put their personal stamp on this lovely home. Possible potential for easy expansion. Transparent pricing. Just blocks from GG Park, Ocean Beach, cafes, restaurants, MUNI. Custom lighting, refinished oak floors, multiple skylights. Bright open plan living/dining room with wood burning fireplace, picture window, hardwood floors. Eat-in kitchen with new stainless refrigerator, gas range, tile floors, overlooking garden. Some ocean views. 2 bright, spacious BRs with good closets, and tiled hall BA with shower/tub, skylight. Entry level foyer leads to the primary garden-facing BR suite with oak floors and en-suite BA w/stall shower. New int/ext paint. Exceptionally deep west-facing garden and patio. Lg garage and lower basement area with excellent possible potential for expansion within envelope, and also possible additional expansion potential. Don't miss this prime starter home in a perfect location!

Welcome home to 1188 Valencia #509! The gorgeous top floor 2 bedroom, 2 bathroom home with stunning views is yours for the taking. Built in 2018 by developer J.S. Sullivan, they sought to bring modern living to the Mission. This home provides views from Bernal Heights through to Twin Peaks! The unit's incredible stainless Steele appliances (Smeg, Bosch, Fisher& Paykel), kitchen layout and functionality afford the host the ability to prep and cook while also engaging with their guest. The newly added pantry and ample storage allow for easy stowage of all of your kitchen gadgets and culinary delights. In unit laundry, in unit AC, Custom electronic window coverings, 1 car parking with personal JuiceBox1 EV charger, 1 storage space, and 1 bike parking spot finish this home.

Top floor Potrero Hill residence checks all the boxes: three spacious bedrooms, two updated bathrooms, and views from every room of the home. The open concept living / dining room has seamless flow from the kitchen which features recent appliance, countertop and flooring upgrades. Washer dryer hook-ups in unit and shared backyard. Ideally situated between shops & restaurants of both Potrero Hill and Dogpatch, with easy access to Caltrain, Muni, and 280 freeway.

Rare Opportunity ! Located at the Corner Building on Russian Hill. Well maintained, 1 Bedroom, 1 Bath with Spacious floor plan, Formal Dining Room, Large Living Room, Good Size Bedroom and Windows all around

This custom-made city retreat is almost invisible from the street & is nestled on a quiet cul-de-sac of sun-soaked Potrero Hill. Tucked behind a private fence, the Japanese inspired home is approached through a rock garden with Japanese maple trees and large stepping stones. Upon entry you are greeted with an open, airy design that mixes modern materials like-integrally-colored cinder block, glass and steel with natural wood. The floor-to ceiling windows and doors have removeable shoji screens. The main level features an open floor plan concept, sunlit kitchen, full bathroom & direct access to the serene backyard with a bubbling pond, bamboo garden and spectacular cherry blossom tree. The lower level of the home has an industrial-style feel with concrete floors, exposed ceilings and the continued cinder block walls. Perfect for a primary suite, this level currently has a half bathroom with the potential to add a spacious spa-like bathroom, & has direct access to the front and backyard.

Delight in urban San Francisco living in this two-level loft style condo in the heart of South Beach. The spacious floor plan features an open floor plan with hardwood flooring, two bathrooms, and a lofted upstairs bedroom with walk-in closet. Exposed concrete, a chef's kitchen with stainless steel appliances, and floor-to-ceiling windows complete the home. 1 car deeded parking. 200 Brannan is a full service building offering 24 hr security, concierge, lushly landscaped courtyard, full fitness center and secure deeded underground parking. A short walk to the neighborhood grocery store, deli, restaurants, shops, and cafes. Easy access to the Financial District, Ferry Building, Farmers Market, world-class restaurants, Chase Center (Go Dubs!), Oracle park (Go Gigantes!), 101, 280, the Bay Bridge, Muni, and CalTrain. *Unit photos coming soon.

Picture-perfect modern pied--terre in Duboce Triangle! Impeccably remodeled 2 bed, 1 bath in quiet 6 unit building just a block from Market & Church. Fresh, chic aesthetic, wonderful light & smart use of space. Open-plan kitchen/living combo w/south-facing bay windows that catch the sun year-round. Gorgeous kitchen remodel w/brand new everything: smokey gray cabinetry, stainless appliances, gas range, glossy subway tile, white quartz counters & huge central dining bar. Wall-to-wall bedroom closets w/Elfa storage & design-savvy mirrored doors that reflect the abundant natural light. Renovated full bath w/soaking tub & shower, lg linen closet & luxe tile work. Lovely new wide-plank hw floors throughout & stacked in-unit w&d. Host a BBQ or pre-dinner drinks on the shared roof deck w/sweeping east, north & west views. Just two blocks to Duboce Park & a quick walk to Lower Haight, Castro, NoPaa sophisticated move-in-ready flat in the heart of city!

Inner Sunset full floor two bedroom one bath condo conveniently located just across from Golden Gate Park, half block to Irving Street eateries and shops, 1.5 blocks to N-Judah MUNI lines, UCSF, & other public transit. It offers spacious front living room with fire place, formal dining room, good-sized kitchen, laundry room/closet off the kitchen, full bath, and two bedrooms in the back overlooking huge yard. Stairs off the kitchen to the full shared garage downstairs. There are plenty of storage spaces plus one car parking for this unit. Low HOA dues with high reserves. Must see!

Dolores Park 1 bedroom 1 bathroom condominium. Combo Living room/dining area. Laundry on site. Central to everything... Blocks to Market Street, Castro and Valencia Street shops and restaurants. Rated 96 out of 100 as Walkable; 100 for Rider's Paradise for Transit; and 99 as Biker's Paradise. Maximum income for 1 person = $107,600; 2 people = $123,000; 3 = $138,350; 4 = $153,700, etc. Must be 1st-time homebuyer & income eligible. See sfmohcd.org for additional program info. Unit available thru the Mayor's Office of Housing and Community Development (MOHCD) & subject to resale controls, monitoring & other restrictions. Unit will be listed on DAHLIA, the SF Housing Portal (https://housing.sfgov.org) starting on the application date, December 18, 2020 . Visit https://housing.sfgov.org for application & program info. Cool Cole Valley is the ideal setting for this charming view condo on Carmel Street. Golden Gate Bridge and Mt. Tam views are on display in this airy and bright unit in a great four-unit corner building. The roomy floor plan includes a large bedroom, a full sunny updated bath, updated kitchen with top of the line appliances including Wolf and Bosch, and a showcase living room with fireplace, hardwood floors, premium fixtures, period details, and plenty of space for dining and for working from home. One car parking in garage with laundry. 160 Carmel is located in the heart of beloved Cole Valley, on a serene, tree-lined block, close to shops, restaurants, schools, hiking trails, the museums and attractions of Golden Gate Park, and transportation, including MUNI N-Judah train and tech shuttle stops.

Rarely available, home built in 1997. Tri-level single family home with lots of natural lights. Main level features vaulted ceiling, living room with fireplace, dining room, remodeled kitchen with Stainless Steel appliances and granite countertops. A deck off the kitchen with access to the level backyard. Top floor features 3 beds and 2 baths. Master bedroom with walk-in closet, double sinks vanity and stall shower. Garage with 2 cars parking and lots of storage spaces. Conveniently located, walk to supermarket and public transportation. Minutes to freeway and restaurants.

Top floor condominium at highly coveted Broderick Place in excellent NOPA location features a large private balcony and an open floor plan design for dining & entertaining. Bright and cheerful home offers a popular split floor plan with bedrooms on either side of the living area, a large kitchen with a breakfast bar with rich deep granite counters, a master suite with a walk-in closet, a second bedroom & guest bath, in-unit washer/dryer + deeded parking. Broderick Place is an elevator building housing Peet's Coffee, Nopalito Mexican Restaurant, & fine grocery shopping at Falletti Foods Market. HOT location is steps to some of the largest open space in San Francisco with direct access to jogging and bike paths along the Panhandle leading to Golden Gate Park. Nearby is Whole Foods, Bi-Rite Market & Divisadero corridor/NOPA cafes & restaurants, public transportation & access to area freeways

address: 77 Van Ness Ave #702, San Francisco, CA 94102
description: What a price! While residing at 77 Van Ness one can enjoy being at the center of both a cultural and transportation hub within San Francisco while owning a fine example of The City's modern architectural movement. This is a building showcasing the harmony of form and function with units that exhibit admirable scale, volume, and unadorned style. Unit 702 is a spacious studio with an in-unit laundry, great natural light, a very functional kitchen with high-end appliances, and elegant finishes throughout. 77 Van Ness has generous amenities: a common view roof deck, fitness center, garage parking, and a lobby concierge Monday-Friday. The proximity to several neighborhoods including Civic Center, Hayes Valley, and the Castro allows for convenient access to a wide variety of cultural, shopping, and dining destinations. Yes, life is good at 77 Van Ness.

On the border of Nob Hill & Russian Hill, this gorgeously renovated, top-floor condo hits all the right notes. Located on the quiet side of the building, the bright and spacious unit boasts an open floor plan with designer kitchen finishes, breakfast bar, dining area and living room with fireplace. The oversized master bedroom has a newly remodeled ensuite and overlooks the courtyard. Down the hall is the other recently completed full bath and second bedroom that's perfect for an office/guest room. The home also features new engineered hardwood floors, skylights, ample closet space and recessed lighting. There is one car deeded parking, deeded storage and plenty of outdoor common areas to entertain including a roof deck. With a 96 walk score, it is centrally located close to all the wonderful shops & restaurants on Polk St, Union St, North Beach, Chinatown, Fisherman's Wharf and Ghiradelli Square. Landmarks, parks and transportation options abound. This one can't be missed!

3 bedroom, 2 full bath, 2 car parking recently remodeled with permits, throughout. Secure, private rear yard, with expansive outdoor balcony, just off the open LR/DR/kitchen. Large, numerous windows give great exposure between indoors and outdoors. Dine alfresco in the open air balcony just through the glass doors from the dining area, ideal for entertaining. The kitchen features premium S/S gas appliances, a center island with sink and generous overhang for comfortable seating, pendant lights, and recessed audio speakers. Expansive master suite on lower level with large walk-in closet, opulent soaking tub, separate shower and direct access to the yard. Bathroom remodels feature suspended cabinets, skylight (upstairs), a premium finishes. Beautifully refinished hardwood floors throughout. Recess LED lighting on dimmers. Coved ceilings, with insets, W/B fpl - combine for distinctly comfortable living. High efficiency gas furnace, HWH, and new electrical panel.

This converted historical storefront is one of a kind; wonderfully updated with a clean and contemporary vibe to rival any new construction development. Imbued with charm and character, the preserved Victorian elements on the exterior complement its timeless finishes throughout. Your private street entrance opens to a spacious living/dining room that flows into the large kitchen which features a beautiful sliding barn door to a double pantry. The two bedrooms each have their own set of french doors opening to a private, exclusive-use patio which extends to a huge shared outdoor space. A large spa-like bathroom completes the space. This home is meticulously outfitted with an integrated Sonos sound system, Nest thermostat, custom electric shades, recessed high-end LED lighting, as well as a full electrical upgrade. Located just one block from the Presidio's acres of stunning grounds and nearby shops and restaurants of Chestnut and Union Streets. Photos are virtually staged.

Stunning panoramic water & Bay Bridge view, award-winning creation by architecture firm Garcia Tamjidi converting 2 BR home to exquisite open plan 1+ BR. Exceptional detail, intimate modern space, flowing with light & expansive south/southeast views from every room. Infinite attention to detail in this art-and-living piece in South Beach's ideal, quiet, boutique building just steps from the Embarcadero. Spacious, walkout, South-facing deck, floating walls w/upper and lower reveals, corner-to-corner wall storage, custom designed soft-close cabinetry, stunning dining table spanning living to dining rooms, exquisitely peaceful & serene baths showcasing Miele, Boffe, Stihl and more. Master BR reveals itself from behind a retractable light-permeating scrim or tucks away behind the screen. Exceptionally thought-out visual lines, clean yet dramatic & warm. One of only 11 homes featured in a SF AIA architectural tour. A must see!

This light-filled, top-floor flat offers the ultimate urban paradise. Located where two of San Francisco's most popular neighborhoods meet, at the junction of Noe Valley and Dolores Heights, this 2-bedroom, 1-bath unit features great space, period details and the perfect combination of turn-of-the century charm and modern convenience. Two spacious bedrooms are found at the front of the unit and the generous living room and updated eat-in kitchen are found at the rear of the flat, conveniently located next to the private west-facing balcony. Highlights include wood floors, in-unit laundry located in a nice sunroom off the kitchen, a refreshed full bath and extra storage. This tenancy-in-common unit is part of a charming four-unit 1908 building in a fantastic location near Dolores Park, Noe's bustling 24th Street, cafes, shops and transportation.

608 Peralta provides the perfect refuge right now. The space itself is tranquil, with an efficient floor plan that lives large. The additional features of direct access to outdoor space, plenty of garage storage and a bonus office make it easy to shelter in place and work from home without sacrifice. With new maple floors, a kitchen with shining Quartz counters and a bath with a new vanity and lighting, the condo is spruced and ready for new occupants. And the location, just steps from one of the city's best open spaces for hiking - Bernal Hill Park - make a safe and socially distanced stroll a spectacular opportunity to enjoy something nothing can take away from a San Franciscan: the amazing views we have of our fair city. Transparent pricing. Sellers paid 900k in 2017 and made over 30k in upgrades.

All-New Full Floor 1,125 sqft Flat 3-Bed 1.5-Bath plus office with W/D in Unit. Brand new remodel, absolutely everything has been done! Huge sunny level backyard on a double wide lot. Common areas in final stages of total renovation. Disclosures available on I.O.

Pied a terre, first home or investment property, this tranquil and fully self-contained condo is located on the second floor of the ever popular Parc Telegraph (Lombard St.) condominiums. Modern kitchen with new appliances (stove, oven, dishwasher, microwave), new light fixtures, fresh paint and carpet. One car parking at 101 Lombard. Enjoy everything this cosmopolitan neighborhood has to offer, including close proximity to Levi's Plaza, the Financial District, the Ferry Building, and public transp. to Oracle Park and Chase Center. Hillstone, Fog City restaurants are steps outside the door, as are all the wonderful eateries and attractions that line the Embarcadero. Walk Score of 96. HOA includes 24-hour doorman, earthquake and building insurance, water, garbage and external building maintenance. Clubroom, gym, and free use of the common laundry! Additional storage in the building available at a nominal charge.

address: 296 Santa Rosa Ave, San Francisco, CA 94112

description: Welcome to Mission Terrace! A fabulous, detached, Four-bedroom, One bath home on the border of four desirable neighborhoods: Sunnyside, Bernal Heights, Glen Park, and Excelsior! The classic formal entryway opens to a large open formal living room, a formal dining room with period details, and view windows that showers the home with lots of natural sunlight. There are 3 large bedrooms and a bathroom in the upper level. The largest bedroom even has a private patio! The lower level has a bonus room and lots of potential to expand as your family needs. TWO car garage. Low maintenance backyard. Do not miss this special home that is close to shopping, restaurants, cafes, the newly renovated Balboa park, tennis courts, playground, dog park and skate board park. BART, MUNI, easy access to 101 & 280 freeways, Whole Foods, Canyon Market and Mission Street bodegas.

address: 201 Folsom St Unit 41B, San Francisco, CA 94105

description: Affordable DETACHED Parkside home built on wider 30 x 120 feet lot located just a block to Taraval Street MUNI lines, Taraval Street shops & restaurants, Parkside Square Playground, Sterngrove, Pine Lake Park, McCoppin Square, Larsen Playground, and Stonestown Galleria. This updated bright and cheery home offers front porch with partial ocean views, west facing living room & dining room, spacious kitchen with side exit to both rear yard and street, 3 bedrooms, & full bath all on the same level. One car garage plus excessive storage spaces below the main level. Floors were newly refinished and interior was painted within the last few years. AGENTS: Please READ agent remarks for showing & offer instructions rather than contacting listing agents. Thank you!

Unique opportunities await in this vacant 2 unit property, ideal for a developer or owner user, ready for thoughtful restoration or personalization. Family occupied and owned for over 65 years and located on a welcoming street in the Mission this could be a single family, TIC, or maintained as a duplex. address: 4515 25th St Unit A, San Francisco, CA 94114

description: This charming Victorian condo in one of the most desirable neighborhoods. This 1 bedroom/1 bathroom property has retained its original charm while offering modern updates. Bay windows, original crown molding, arched entrances, wooden flooring, a decorative fireplace and an abundance of light make this condo an inviting and cozy home. There are shared storage and washer/dryer in the common area and a shared backyard. For your peace of mind and very rare: the building has earthquake insurance. This is the quintessential San Francisco location: few blocks away from Alamo Square, with its beautiful Painted Ladies and downtown vistas, only a block away from the happening Divisadero corridor and close to Hayes Valley and Haight Ashbury.

As one of the most iconic residential buildings in Pacific Heights, Broadway Towers is a renowned example of the mid-century aesthetic in the heart of the north side. With floor to ceiling windows across the entire home, this 1 bed / 1 bath home is bright and flooded with light. Relax or work from home on your private terrace that spans the entire width of the unit. The oversized living and dining room have a peekaboo view of the Golden Gate Bridge and direct walkout to the terrace. In the bedroom, walk out to your private terrace and take advantage of the large, walk-in closet. Updated, modern kitchen and bathroom. Freshly painted, with new carpet and blinds. Doorman building with professional building management and one-car parking. HOA includes professional management, water, cable, radiant heat, building insurance and earthquake insurance. All the best of Pacific Heights, Cow Hollow and the Marina are within walking distance.

Delight in urban San Francisco living in this two-level loft style condo in the heart of South Beach. The spacious floor plan features an open floor plan with hardwood flooring, two bathrooms, and a lofted upstairs bedroom with walk-in closet. Exposed concrete, a chef's kitchen with stainless steel appliances, and floor-to-ceiling windows complete the home. 1 car deeded parking. 200 Brannan is a full service building offering 24 hr security, concierge, lushly landscaped courtyard, full fitness center and secure deeded underground parking. A short walk to the neighborhood grocery store, deli, restaurants, shops, and cafes. Easy access to the Financial District, Ferry Building, Farmers Market, world-class restaurants, Chase Center (Go Dubs!), Oracle park (Go Gigantes!), 101, 280, the Bay Bridge, Muni, and CalTrain. *Unit photos coming soon.

75K Price Reduction. Two homes on one lot. Room for ADU expansion as one unit contains two kitchens. Ideally located homes just two blocks from Ocean Beach. Low maintenance corner lot with two garages. Each home has a separate meter, heating system. Both homes are leased with solid financials and stable tenants. Some remodeling in both homes. Recently painted. Combined rents over $6000/monthly. Steps to Ocean Beach and N Judah. Nearby coffee shops include Java Beach Cafe, Andytown Coffee Roasters and Bubble Tea & Dessert Cafe. Neighboring restaurants include Golden Gate, Thanh Long and Thai Cottage.

Priced to sell! Nestled in the North Waterfront area, this 6th floor, one bedroom condo with a partial view of the bay, is move in ready! There are new stainless steel appliances in the galley style kitchen, a newly painted interior and an updated bathroom. 1 car parking in building garage. Amenities include a 24 hr front desk security, a remodeled gym, complimentary laundry facilities, a club room with a kitchen and library, and a guest suite that can be reserved for visitors. With a walk score of 90, you're conveniently close to the Bay Club, Financial District, the Waterfront, Embarcadero, Farmers Market and North Beach.

Spacious 1 Bedroom home at LagunaHayes, a boutique building anchored in the heart of Hayes Valley, one of San Francisco's most coveted neighborhoods. Perfectly situated on the corner of Laguna and Hayes with ground floor retail and walking distance to boutiques, cafes, & restaurants. Enjoy modern living with this open floorplan, tall ceilings, and inspiring western light. The residences benefit from warm light beaming through custom glass entry doors facing the courtyard. Wide plank white oak floors. Designer Kitchen: Bosch & Miele appliances, Studio Becker cabinets, and quartz countertops. In-unit Washer/Dryer. Custom closet organizers. Central A/C! Common areas include stylish lobby, landscaped center courtyard, furnished rooftop deck with gas grill and iconic San Francisco views! Reasonably-priced parking space in the building, is leased directly from the developer. Many storage options in the unit in addition to a generously-sized deeded storage unit. Bike parking room in bldg.

Newly Constructed Luxury Residence! Offering 3 bedrooms + Den, 3.5 bathrooms, 1-car parking and multiple outdoor spaces. Designer finishes and high-end appliances, custom cabinetry, oak floors, Ann Sacks tile with an open and airy flow with ample ceiling height. All of these elements combine to create an urban retreat that is tranquil and replenishing. www.parkpacificsf.com for more information. Virtually Staged

Ocean View Two Unit Building! Both units include a bright living room, large eat-in kitchen, full bath with stall shower and separate tub, and two generous bedrooms. Vacant lower unit freshly painted, and hardwood floors throughout. Upper unit tenant occupied. Building exterior recently painted, newer furnaces and water heaters. Large level lot with deep, mature garden. Two car side by side parking, shared washer/dryer in garage, storage closet and storage room for owner. Interior staircase from garage to units with covered skylight. Excellent Location near shops and restaurants, MUNI, Zoo, GG Park, running trails, and the beach.

205 Carl St was renovated 'down to the studs' w/ seismic upgrades (steel moment frame, foundation upgraded visible in garage). This 2-level unit features 3 spacious BRs, 2.5 BAs, 1 car SbyS parking and storage. The main level consists of an open floor plan, granite, stainless, gas kitchen, 2 BR and 1.5 BA. The lower lvl features a beautiful master suite with a gorgeous BA and spacious closet. Beautiful HW floors. Leased Tesla Solar system - see disclosures for details. Just outside the master is a unique garden seating area with incredible ambience, exclusive use. The other areas of the yard are common. Walk to tech stops/MUNI. Cole Valley is a distinct neighborhood with shopping, GG Park, major hospitals and other conveniences just steps away.

Have it all with this absolute dream home in the heart of Bernal Heights! 8 Montezuma is a one-of-a-kind condo that offers 2BD, 1BA, a private parking garage, an exclusive lush yard + patio, storage, laundry, and of course... views! The 2 spacious bedrooms enjoy captivating outlooks from the classic bay windows of the dazzling city skyline and Twin Peaks. The inviting entertaining area enjoys marvelous afternoon light and opens up to a magical alfresco escape where a deeded garden terrace boasts golden sunsets. This sun-kissed garden and patio space is the perfect place for a zoom call, barbecue party, or just simply to enjoy the birdsong and butterflies. Back inside, the efficient kitchen is outfitted with an eat-in area, garden views, and stainless steel appliances including a new gas stove and dishwasher. Live the Bernal lifestyle, close to the best of SF restaurants & cafes, numerous parks, freeways and transportation.

PRICE DROPPED. Probate Sale, Court Confirmation Not Required, Building will be delivered vacant, 3 units: 672, 672A and 674 Hampshire St, Great opportunity for investor. Minutes to 280, 101, public transportation.

Wow! You have to see this absolutely huge remodeled Victorian condo in coveted Cole Valley! Boasting 3 generous bedrooms & 2 remodeled baths, this 1929 square foot condo has it all! Comfy living room w/decorative fireplace & period light fixtures, stylish eat-in kitchen w/quartz counters, stainless appliances, abundant cabinets & breakfast nook. Formal dining room has period built-ins, plate rack, antique tiled fireplace, & greenbelt outlooks. These are good sized bedrooms which get great light. 2 full tiled baths W/shower over tub & stall shower, Stone top cabinet vanities & good storage. Walk out deck from the kitchen, overlooking the lush garden. Great spot for your BBQ & cafe table. There are sparkling hardwood flrs thru out, soaring ceilings & charming Victorian details. Garage parking, tons of storage, interior access from garage. Walk out to the best Cole Valley has to offer, from shops to restaurants, tech shuttles, public transportation, close to Whole Foods. Walk to GG Park.

address: 1688 Pine St Unit W1002, San Francisco, CA 94109
description: Elegant and light filled corner residence at the popular Rockwell! This spacious unit with an open layout awaits your creativity. Accommodating stainless steel appliances in the kitchen gives it a modern look with a balcony overseeing beautiful San Francisco city lights. A modern 2 bedroom, 2 bathroom with plenty of closets for all your storage needs. Residences at the Rockwell and their guests can enjoy the exclusive use of a full suite of resort-class amenities including a 24 hour concierge, fully equipped gym, BBQ area, and a fabulous penthouse club room with kitchenette and terrace featuring City views, fire-pits and wonderful lounging areas. The ground level community room with kitchenette steps out onto the interior courtyard and is perfect for hosting business conferences or social events. The location is excellent, with Whole Foods next door and walking distance to public transportation!

334 Holladay Avenue is a light & bright 3 bedroom, 2 bathroom Bernal Heights' home boasting a flexible floor plan with multiple outdoor spaces. A large, sunny deck with room for outdoor seating welcomes you inside to seamless a living-dining flow. The updated kitchen features stainless steel appliances and ample cabinet space. Upstairs you'll find two bedrooms and a stunning new bathroom. The first floor offers a flexile floor plan with room for a home office, workout room, or an additional family lounge space. Make your way outside to a spacious and private backyard with room for BBQ and multiple seating areas. Complete with 1 car garage parking and tasteful finishes and updates throughout. Located minutes to Cortland Ave shops & dining, local parks, and freeways - Welcome to life in Bernal Heights!

Relish an elevated level of living in this top-floor 2 bed / 1 bath home in NOPA with modern convenience and 1920's charm. Enjoy it all: chef's kitchen, formal dining room, in-unit laundry, storage room and 1-car parking. Enter up the stairwell into the landing that graciously opens into the window-lined, tranquil living room; this is the heart of your home. A bespoke arched ceiling invites you into the spacious dining room. Your gourmet kitchen has all the right ingredients to cook with ease: stainless steel appliances, ample countertops, cabinetry and an impeccable Bertazzoni stove with vented hood. Transitioning into the hallway is your generously-sized bathroom with rain shower and marble surround. Your two bedrooms feature designer detail, full closets, and natural light from their oversized windows. The building's expansive, landscaped backyard is truly an impressive oasis. Just steps to the Panhandle and amazing shops, cafes and in-demand eateries. Don't miss!

address: 1186 Eddy St Unit B, San Francisco, CA 94109
description: Live the San Francisco life in a picturesque Cathedral Hill location just across from Jefferson Square Park! If you are looking for a bright, modern two bedroom, two bath condo with low HOA dues this home is for you. It's freshly painted throughout with an open concept living & dining room area including an updated kitchen that boasts lovely granite countertops and stainless steel appliances. The home includes a front patio area, intercom system, plus free in-building laundry, and there is shared rooftop terrace for those relaxing moments. You will be living in a gated property that comes complete with a generously sized designated parking spot and storage space inside a secured garage. This property is also in close proximity to Japantown, Fillmore District, Civic Center, Hayes Valley, and the new CPMC Campus. Virtual tour https://my.matterport.com/show/?m=mjBvEsg2ta6

This live/work corner unit loft located in the trendy Mission District offers tons of light and dramatic floor-to-ceiling windows with 14+ foot high ceilings in the airy living room. Loft has two separate entrances, one on 17th Street and the other from inside the building, making this the ideal place to work or run a business from home. The main floor is built around entertaining with an open-plan layout, featuring open concept living room and dining area, chef's kitchen with new cabinets and quartz countertops, full bath and washer/dryer hook ups. The bedroom is upstairs, creating a private retreat with ensuite bathroom and walk-in closet. This unit also includes an assigned parking space in a secure covered garage with private storage and access to a shared courtyard with barbecue. HOA dues includes water, garbage, management, exterior maintenance and building insurance.

Contemporary light and bright unit with high ceilings and a desirable floor plan at Arterra, a LEED Silver building completed in 2009 in the heart of Mission Bay. One bed, one bath plus bonus den/dining space and formal entryway, with beautiful bamboo floors. The west-facing views from the 15th floor do not disappoint. The kitchen features stainless steel appliances and the unit features in-unit laundry and a deeded parking spot. There are generous closets in the bedroom and entryway. Enjoy the community rooftop deck with BBQ and the community herb garden, as well as the luxury of a 24-hour attended lobby. Additional amenities (currently closed for COVID) include a community room, guest suite and fitness center. Conveniently located near CalTrain, MUNI and 280/101.

High on Bernal sits this lovely 1950s home that epitomizes mid-century style and history. Originally a two bedroom, one bath on a large 2,500 square foot lot, this home has been lovingly expanded to four bedrooms and three baths over two levels. The entire upper level living area has hardwood floors and includes three bedrooms, two bathrooms, an updated kitchen with Corian countertops, and dining area. A private wooden deck was added off the third bedroom. The lower level was expanded to include an additional room that could be used as a fourth bedroom, den or office and third bathroom. Both levels enjoy access to a lengthy flat yard, perfect for entertaining and relaxing. There is a one-car garage, work area and plenty of storage. This lovely home is just a short stroll to the top of Bernal Hill and perfectly situated between the shops and restaurants on Cortland and Precita Park. Close to public transportation and highways 101 and 280.

Bright and spacious 2 bedroom penthouse level home at the Palms! Fantastic floor plan with split bedrooms and 2 full baths (one en-suite). The sizable master bedroom offers 2 closets with room for a king size bed, seating area and dressers. Studio Becker cabinetry in the kitchen and both bathrooms, quartz counters along with Sub-Zero & Bosch appliances. The home offers expansive floor-to-ceiling windows in each room and the east facing deck allows for stunning downtown views. Custom lighting, built out closets and hardwood floors can be found throughout the home along with designer paint and finishes. It's a wonderful city home that's not to be missed! The building offers a 24-hour lobby attendant, concierge, fitness center, business center, theater, club lounge, and outdoor courtyard. One-car parking is included but with a 95 walk score and easy access to Whole Foods, dozens of restaurants and both Muni and Caltrain, you're likely to never drive your car.
For Comp Purposes Only

3 bedroom, 2 full bath, 2 car parking recently remodeled with permits, throughout. Secure, private rear yard, with expansive outdoor balcony, just off the open LR/DR/kitchen. Large, numerous windows give great exposure between indoors and outdoors. Dine alfresco in the open air balcony just through the glass doors from the dining area, ideal for entertaining. The kitchen features premium S/S gas appliances, a center island with sink and generous overhang for comfortable seating, pendant lights, and recessed audio speakers. Expansive master suite on lower level with large walk-in closet, opulent soaking tub, separate shower and direct access to the yard. Bathroom remodels feature suspended cabinets, skylight (upstairs), a premium finishes. Beautifully refinished hardwood floors throughout. Recess LED lighting on dimmers. Coved ceilings, with insets, W/B fpl - combine for distinctly comfortable living. High efficiency gas furnace, HWH, and new electrical panel.

This live/work corner unit loft located in the trendy Mission District offers tons of light and dramatic floor-to-ceiling windows with 14+ foot high ceilings in the airy living room. Loft has two separate entrances, one on 17th Street and the other from inside the building, making this the ideal place to work or run a business from home. The main floor is built around entertaining with an open-plan layout, featuring open concept living room and dining area, chef's kitchen with new cabinets and quartz countertops, full bath and washer/dryer hook ups. The bedroom is upstairs, creating a private retreat with ensuite bathroom and walk-in closet. This unit also includes an assigned parking space in a secure covered garage with private storage and access to a shared courtyard with barbecue. HOA dues includes water, garbage, management, exterior maintenance and building insurance.

All-New Full Floor 1,140 sqft Flat 3-Bed 2-Bath plus office with W/D in Unit. Please follow link to 3D Tour. Brand new remodel, absolutely everything has been done! Huge sunny level backyard on a double wide lot. Cross street is 20th where all the best Inner Mission cafes and restaurants are (Flour & Water, Atlas cafe, Sightglass, etc). One-car private garage available for $100K 3D tour linked above. Common areas in final stages of total renovation. Disclosures available on I.O.

Stunning Upper Floor Corner Unit, 2 en-suite bedrooms w/walk-in custom closets & 2ba. Only 1 of 2 units in the building w/ an exclusive, HUGE walk-out patio, 575 sqft. Perfect for outdoor activities. Wall of windows w/designer auto shades make this 1,450+sqft unit feel even bigger & brighter. Main living & dining areas are framed by a newly updated open chef's kitchen w/center island & breakfast bar. New counters, backsplash, stainless steel appliances, updated baths, fresh paint & convenient in-unit washer/dryer. Shipley Square, a boutique mid-rise building next to Yerba Buena/Soma. Elevator building, Rooftop Deck, 1 deeded large parking space & Bicycle Storage. This location is what city living is all about - convenience, fine dining, arts, culture & luxury. Walk score of 97 - Whole Foods, Yerba Buena Gardens, Metreon Center, specialty coffee & a variety of outdoor dining spots. The new 4th St Muni Metro Station, Ferry Building, Oracle Park & Mission Bay are steps away. All informati

This 2 bed, 1 bath Central Richmond home affords a plenitude of possibilities. Abounding in original details throughout, including elegant tray ceilings, a brick fireplace, French doors, and custom built-ins, 1721 Cabrillo is a home that leaves a lasting impression. The formal foyer welcomes you into a sundrenched living room. The generous seating area is anchored by a stately fireplace with a built-in shelving surround. Through the French doors, you are met with an airy formal dining room complete with a built-in buffet. The charming & sunny eat-in kitchen encompasses plenty of cabinet space. Designed with comfort top of mind, the home invites you to make the most of every resting moment with two sizable bedrooms and a full bath. The expansive first floor is home to a 2-car garage, ample storage, a bonus room & a large laundry area with access to an expansive backyard with plenty of room to garden and relax. Located blocks from GGP, restaurants, cafes & public transit.

Not your everyday downtown condo! Stylish and serene with a rare spacious private patio and peaceful urban vibe! This one is in the BACK of the building, NOT on Bush. Freshly painted with newly refinished hardwood floors. Clean lines showcase the open floor plan. The efficient kitchen with new appliances has counter height seating and is open to the living/dining area. Direct access to a generous private patio. The restful bedroom has outlooks to the patio and courtyard. The high-touch high-service La Galleria HOA amenities include 24/7 lobby attendants/security, professionally landscaped courtyard perfect for socially distant outdoor gatherings or work from home outside. One-car garage parking. On-site laundry (credit card-enabled). Storage space available for rent. Convenience is key and rated with 99 Walkscore®. Easy access to Union Square and the Financial District.

Dramatic and flexible 1 Bedroom + Den, 2 full Bathroom floorplan and an abundance of South Facing, natural light combine to create a sophisticated urban home located in burgeoning central SOMA. Spacious enough to social distance, this meticulously maintained live/work loft comes replete with numerous modern amenities including gleaming hardwood floors, multiple skylights, chef's kitchen with SS appliances, gas range, gas fireplace and a walk-in closet. The flexible Den space can cross function as home office, Zoom Room or guest sleeping area. Additional recent upgrades include freshly painted cabinets, newly installed window treatments and designer lighting package throughout. In-unit W/D, HUGE onsite storage, 1 car full size garage parking space and low HOA dues complete the package for this ultimate City abode. Convenient SOMA location with easy access to countless neighborhood amenities and eateries, 280/101, Embarcadero waterfront and San Francisco's sunniest micro climate.

address: 25 Santa Rosa Ave, San Francisco, CA 94112
description: A grand, gracious, and extraordinary home with a gorgeous facade, oversized lot, located in a truly special Mission Terrace location! The impressive and inviting front steps lead to a timeless front door that opens to a combination of new possibilities and a glimpse of a stately past steeped in period detail. The home opens to a dramatic foyer that separates the study from the impressive living room, three large bedrooms, a full bathroom, two half bathrooms, a regal dining room, a large kitchen area, and all are graced with plenty of natural light from this semi-attached home. There is an enormous lower level/basement area that offers the potential for future expansion, a long and private driveway with plenty of parking, and a garage. The backyard offers a private and verdant setting and a detached garage with possible potential for future expansion. The vacant lot next door is also for sale offering a potential buyer the opportunity to own both parcels and a coveted outdoor space!
SOMA Loft, Great Location, Private Street. Top Floor Unit w/Skylight. Freshly Painted. Carpets + Hardwood Floor.

Wow! You have to see this absolutely huge remodeled Victorian condo in coveted Cole Valley! Boasting 3 generous bedrooms & 2 remodeled baths, this 1929 square foot condo has it all! Comfy living room w/decorative fireplace & period light fixtures, stylish eat-in kitchen w/quartz counters, stainless appliances, abundant cabinets & breakfast nook. Formal dining room has period built-ins, plate rack, antique tiled fireplace, & greenbelt outlooks. These are good sized bedrooms which get great light. 2 full tiled baths W/shower over tub & stall shower, Stone top cabinet vanities & good storage. Walk out deck from the kitchen, overlooking the lush garden. Great spot for your BBQ & cafe table. There are sparkling hardwood flrs thru out, soaring ceilings & charming Victorian details. Garage parking, tons of storage, interior access from garage. Walk out to the best Cole Valley has to offer, from shops to restaurants, tech shuttles, public transportation, close to Whole Foods. Walk to GG Park.

address: 4515 25th St Unit A, San Francisco, CA 94114
description: Spectacular luxuriously remodeled Noe Valley modern 2 BR & 2 BA residence. This stunning property features 10' ceilings, & red oak flooring throughout. The bright LR provides ample space w/ custom fireplace, & the adjacent dining area is ready for guests w/ custom built-in banquette. In the kitchen, the white oak cabinet are topped by white marble which surround the centerpiece six-burner Blue Star range. Wraparound stainless shelving help keep the counter clear, & a Miele refrigerator, dishwasher, & deep sink complete the room. The hall BA includes a bamboo cabinet, blue slate flooring, & shower over tub. The spacious master bath w/ slate floors & walls, soaking tub, rain shower, radiant heating, & 2 sinks built on a Kamani wood counter. 2 generous bedrooms open to the sunny, deeded 2 level deck. Modern, Le Grande Adorne light switches & outlets throughout. In unit laundry & 2 car pkg plus storage complete this special residence just blocks away from the 24th Street shops/restaurants.

Admirers of the popular annual Portola District Garden Tour most likely have visited the meandering hillside garden of this property. If you have not seen it, you must...as well as the lovely home & views that are included. This 1955(per tax data) gem is a special sanctuary. Perched high on a cul-de-sac st, this updated home offers mesmerizing views & romanced outdoor living w/a deep lot. The main lvl offers 2 bedrooms, remodeled BA, living room & eat-in kitchen w/direct walk-out to a large rear deck for alfresco dining and entertaining w/evening views over the city as the back drop. The lower lvl offers bonus space, BA and large closet. Sellers used this space as a 3rd bedroom. Below the deck is another outdoor lounging area & gardener's potting area. The upper grassy yard is fenced & perfect for Fido while the down-sloped yard beyond the upper picket fence is where the magic happens. Fruit trees, artichokes, herbs, flowers, hummingbirds, sitting areas and raised planter veggies await

Spacious, updated, safe, secure, and ultimately walkable to best of the Mission District. 633 Capp Street bundles everything desirable about living in San Francisco into one complete package. Featuring a tastefully modern kitchen with gorgeous stone countertops & brand new appliances, the open concept kitchen/living offers the best possible arrangement of living space. The fantastic layout provides two large bedrooms and one well-appointed bathroom - all accented by high ceilings, hardwood flooring throughout, and an abundance of natural light. This boutique TIC building also provides a landscaped private getaway backyard space, a recent foundation retrofit, new roof, updated security gates & video doorbell, laundry room, 1 car parking, and a huge private storage room. Just steps from the vibrant Valencia corridor, and walking distance to 24th Street, local restaurants and dining, Dolores Park, BART, MUNI & more, this residence checks all the boxes!

Top floor Potrero Hill residence checks all the boxes: three spacious bedrooms, two updated bathrooms, and views from every room of the home. The open concept living / dining room has seamless flow from the kitchen which features recent appliance, countertop and flooring upgrades. Washer dryer hook-ups in unit and shared backyard. Ideally situated between shops & restaurants of both Potrero Hill and Dogpatch, with easy access to Caltrain, Muni, and 280 freeway.

Beautiful Light Filled Corner Flat in Prime Location! On the cusp of Cole Valley, this spacious, light filled, two bedroom Upper Haight corner flat will make you swoon! Gorgeous period details throughout stained glass, soaring ceilings, warm wood floors, and crown molding. Sun drenched, spacious living room with corner rotunda space lined with windows, and a decorative fireplace. Formal dining room with box beam ceilings, a second decorative fireplace and bay windows perfect for entertaining. Bright eat-in kitchen with butcher block counters, and plenty of work and storage space. Two spacious bedrooms with ample closet space. Updated, full tiled bath and in-unit laundry. Ideal location: 97 WalkScore walk to world class Haight and Cole Valley shops, cafes, and restaurants. Three minute walk to Golden Gate Park, and around the corner from Whole Foods. 97 BikeScore bike to the beach! Steps to the N-Judah and tech shuttles. Easy street parking. The whole package!

Charming Jr 1-BR at Beacon showcasing amazing downtown skyline & Twin Peaks views! The living space has a built in wall shelf creating an airy feel with the opportunity to add decor or storage. An open wall to the bedroom provides ample light & creative living, effortlessly dividing the room into a separated bedroom alcove w custom shades for privacy. It creates a meaningful sense of space & provides a relaxing place of rest feat. large walk in closet w custom drawers. Bathroom has additional storage closet & upgraded bath glass enclosure. This city lover's dream home is complete w W&D, Earthquake Insurance & 1 secured pkg. 5-star amenities; 24/7 drman security, heated outdoor pool & spas, sauna, clubhouse w/kitchen, gym, business ctr & outdoor dog park. Just steps frm Caltrain, Muni & future Central Subway. Short walk to Ferry Bldg/Farmer's Market, Embarcadero Waterfront, SOMA, Fidi, Union Square. Prime location near Freeways, BART, buses, tech/free shuttle to FiDi, EastBay/Peninsula.

Extensive luxury amenities and a convenient central location in Mission Bay make The Beacon one of San Francisco's premier residences. A 24-hour doorman greets you on the way into an urban retreat offering: heated swimming pool, hot tub, sauna, state-of-the-art gym, private dog park, clubhouse with catering kitchen, business center complete with conference room, and even a security robot named Rosie. #645 is a sunny one-bedroom condominium with stainless steel appliances, hardwood floors, an in-unit washer/dryer, and incredible unobstructed southwestern views of Twin Peaks. A generous walk-in closet, custom black-out shades, designated parking, and a Ring doorbell complete this home.

Welcome home to 1188 Valencia #509! The gorgeous top floor 2 bedroom, 2 bathroom home with stunning views is yours for the taking. Built in 2018 by developer J.S. Sullivan, they sought to bring modern living to the Mission. This home provides views from Bernal Heights through to Twin Peaks! The unit's incredible stainless Steele appliances (Smeg, Bosch, Fisher& Paykel), kitchen layout and functionality afford the host the ability to prep and cook while also engaging with their guest. The newly added pantry and ample storage allow for easy stowage of all of your kitchen gadgets and culinary delights. Elegant wide plank oak floors span the living spaces while plush carpet welcome guests to each of their bedroom retreats. In unit laundry, in unit AC, Custom electronic window coverings, 1 car parking with personal JuiceBox1 EV charger, 1 storage space, and 1 bike parking spot finish this home.

Welcome to 451 Kansas, #392 at The Potrero. This bright south and east-facing corner 2 bed/2 bath residence checks all the boxes. Features include an open living/dining area, hardwood flooring throughout, an en suite master, a second bedroom with adjacent bath, and a large exclusive use enclosed patio. The Potrero is a secured, 165-unit, courtyard complex located in one of San Francisco's most desirable neighborhoods and is well known for exceptional livability. With Whole Foods just downstairs, residents can do their grocery shopping, dine or grab a cup of coffee without ever leaving the property. What's more, the location affords great weather and easy access to freeways, downtown, and waterfront attractions. The property features deeded parking in a secured garage, beautifully landscaped walkways and courtyards, fitness facilities, and a rooftop deck with fantastic views.

334 Holladay Avenue is a light & bright 3 bedroom, 2 bathroom Bernal Heights' home boasting a flexible floor plan with multiple outdoor spaces. A large, sunny deck with room for outdoor seating welcomes you inside to seamless a living-dining flow. The updated kitchen features stainless steel appliances and ample cabinet space. Upstairs you'll find two bedrooms and a stunning new bathroom. The first floor offers a flexile floor plan with room for a home office, workout room, or an additional family lounge space. Make your way outside to a spacious and private backyard with room for BBQ and multiple seating areas. Complete with 1 car garage parking and tasteful finishes and updates throughout. Located minutes to Cortland Ave shops & dining, local parks, and freeways - Welcome to life in Bernal Heights!

Fall in love with this beautiful home located in the desirable Mission District. Just steps away from James Rolph Playground and Potrero del Sol Community Garden, this beautifully remodeled home is everything you have been looking for! Flexible and easy-living floor plan offers 2 spacious bedrooms, cozy living room with new laminate flooring, remodeled kitchen and bathroom on the main level. Work from home? Extended family visits? Don't miss the downstairs in-law unit featuring one bedroom, full bathroom, kitchenette and living area that makes room for extended family, or can lease out for extra income! One off street parking spot, as well as one full car garage. Laundry closet on site. Good size backyard, great for entertaining. Don't miss out on this great opportunity!

Penthouse level 1BR 1BR 1PKG at The Palms San Francisco. A full amenities building with a 24-hour lobby attendant, breathtaking lobby, Owner's Lounge to reserve for parties and events, Fitness Center with yoga room, business center and conference room, and a private theater to reserve. This well priced unit has been repainted top to bottom, has new carpet in the large bedroom. Kitchen has tile floors, Custom Cabinets, Subzero Refrigerator, Bosch gas cooktop and built in oven, Bosch dishwasher, quartz countertops raised breakfast bar and in-unit stacked washer and dryer. Wood floors in living/dining looking out a large glass sliding door to balcony and landscaped courtyard. This property gets a lot of natural light. Parking, included in the price, is on the first floor close to elevator. On site Management and Low HOA dues enhance being a resident at the Palms.

Chic two bedroom, two bath modern condominium with parking at Rowan. This inviting open plan with stunning downtown and city views from the floor to ceiling windows offers a contemporary living experience. The chef's kitchen is outfitted with Domus and Domus cabinets, caesarstone counters and high-end stainless Bertazonni, Bosch and Liebherr appliances. Additional features include air conditioning, wide plank white oak floors, smart NEST thermostat, in-unit laundry, and additional storage. Designed by famed Handel Architects, this style uniquely incorporates an exoskeleton design with exposed concrete elements. Common area amenities include a lobby attendant, two high-speed elevators, BBQ stations, fire pit and a stunning roof terrace with panoramic City views. Conveniently located between Potrero Hill and the Inner Mission -- both neighborhoods with some of the best weather in the City. Minutes to prime dining, shopping, highways, public transit and tech shuttles. Walk Score 95.

Fantastic views, Fantastic building, Fantastic Location. Open floor plan that leads to a view deck, probably the most straight shot to downtown cityscape,a view like no other. This well-maintained 2 bedroom/1 bath condo has lovely hardwood floors, good separation of bedrooms, a cool modern wood-burning fireplace a wonderful street in North Bernal Heights between Precita Park and Bernal Heights Park. Easy highway and MUNI access. The 67 Bus will take you almost from your door to BART. Two doors over, there is a public staircase that leads to Harrison St. and down to Precita Park with its wonderful playground and Precita Park Cafe.

Welcome to 477 Roosevelt Way! This beautiful garden unit is nestled on top of Corona Heights. This remodeled 2BR+office, 1 bath condo offers views of the East Bay. Constructed in 1932, this Classic Mediterranean condo combines indoor and outdoor living. Once you walk in, you are greeted with lots of natural light throughout. The bathroom features heated towel rack, wood vanity and shower over tub. Remodeled kitchen has beautiful marble counters, Bosch refrigerator, dishwasher, stove with hood, kitchen island, great cabinet space and a huge pantry. This condo also comes with LED recessed lighting throughout, in-unit washer dryer, 1 car deeded parking, additional storage and a great deeded deck as well as shared garden.

Beautiful spacious 2-level top-floor unit with style, character and abundant light! 3-4 bedrooms, 10-ft. cove ceilings, crown molding, wainscoting and inlaid oak floors. Working fireplace & original glass hutch make the living/ dining room the heart of the home. French Country eat-in kitchen w/ farmhouse sink and softwood floors provide a fabulous space to create and entertain. Parlor doors divide 2 bedrooms or open for a light-filled bedroom / living room. Work-from-home options: Tuck a home office into the knotty-pine porch or use the finished attic space as an office and bedroom. Views of Twin Peaks, Bernal Hill and north to downtown from the upper deck. Large garage w/1-car independent parking and plenty of storage. Enjoy the secluded quiet garden with Meyer lemon tree and fountain. In-unit washer/ dryer. Nest thermostat. Great location, close to shopping, dining and transportation. Also available to purchase entire building. Handsome, move in ready. MUST SEE to appreciate.

Completely renovated Oceanview Single family house features a total of 3 bedrooms; 3 full baths; family room; study room and 1 car parking garage. Large manicured backyard. Deck overlooking the hillside with beautiful sparking neighborhood light at night. Ample of storage space up in the attic. Brand new central heating system; water heater; 10 foot ceiling in kitchen; living and dining room. Bathrooms, flooring, windows (except for the one in attic) walls with insulations. This large lot allows a good distance from your neighbors and many more.....this house is like a new build you don't want to miss. Easy access to freeway, ocean view playground is just right across the street. Don't miss this opportunity.

Delight in urban San Francisco living in this two-level loft style condo in the heart of South Beach. The spacious floor plan features an open floor plan with hardwood flooring, two bathrooms, and a lofted upstairs bedroom with walk-in closet. Exposed concrete, a chef's kitchen with stainless steel appliances, and floor-to-ceiling windows complete the home. 1 car deeded parking. 200 Brannan is a full service building offering 24 hr security, concierge, lushly landscaped courtyard, full fitness center and secure deeded underground parking. A short walk to the neighborhood grocery store, deli, restaurants, shops, and cafes. Easy access to the Financial District, Ferry Building, Farmers Market, world-class restaurants, Chase Center (Go Dubs!), Oracle park (Go Gigantes!), 101, 280, the Bay Bridge, Muni, and CalTrain. *Unit photos coming soon.

Tucked away on a San Francisco greenbelt block, elevated from the street with partial city views this four bedroom two bathroom fully detached home has much to offer. Your guests will give you raving reviews for the combined living, eating and cooking space that flows effortlessly to a private deck with water feature. Trellised seating area has fairy tale like mature foliage. Relax with friends in one of a few seating areas in the back yard. The renovated kitchen has newer appliances and ample counter space. Guest bathroom doubles as powder room for entertaining. Spacious master bedroom with city views and ensuite bathroom with jacuzzi jet tub. Two additional bedrooms on the main level are enough for the whole family. There is a secluded, first floor home office or guest bedroom with enough space for work from home or your own start-up! The hidden meditation-yoga-pilates loft space over the garage will delight you. High garage ceilings and wide spacing allows for two larger vehicles.

This custom-made city retreat is almost invisible from the street & is nestled on a quiet cul-de-sac of sun-soaked Potrero Hill. Tucked behind a private fence, the Japanese inspired home is approached through a rock garden with Japanese maple trees and large stepping stones. Upon entry you are greeted with an open, airy design that mixes modern materials like-integrally-colored cinder block, glass and steel with natural wood. The floor-to ceiling windows and doors have removeable shoji screens. The main level features an open floor plan concept, sunlit kitchen, full bathroom & direct access to the serene backyard with a bubbling pond, bamboo garden and spectacular cherry blossom tree. The lower level of the home has an industrial-style feel with concrete floors, exposed ceilings and the continued cinder block walls. Perfect for a primary suite, this level currently has a half bathroom with the potential to add a spacious spa-like bathroom, & has direct access to the front and backyard.

Contemporary, chic, and captivating top floor home with a large and private outdoor space overlooking amazing downtown and San Francisco Bay views located in the dynamic Dogpatch district! The living/dining area is accentuated with modern accents including freshly painted concrete floors, soaring ceilings, a conveniently located bathroom, an updated gourmet, eat-in kitchen with new countertops and appliances, along with a wall of windows cascading the area with natural light and looking out towards the view. The upper level has a private bedroom area with an updated bathroom, laundry closet, gorgeous wood floors and a dramatic stairway that leads to the inviting and exclusive outdoor space/patio. There is also deeded parking in this well-maintained building. Do not miss this special home that is close to everything!

Bright and spacious 2 bedroom penthouse level home at the Palms! Fantastic floor plan with split bedrooms and 2 full baths (one en-suite). The sizable master bedroom offers 2 closets with room for a king size bed, seating area and dressers. Studio Becker cabinetry in the kitchen and both bathrooms, quartz counters along with Sub-Zero & Bosch appliances. The home offers expansive floor-to-ceiling windows in each room and the east facing deck allows for stunning downtown views. Custom lighting, built out closets and hardwood floors can be found throughout the home along with designer paint and finishes. It's a wonderful city home that's not to be missed! The building offers a 24-hour lobby attendant, concierge, fitness center, business center, theater, club lounge, and outdoor courtyard. One-car parking is included but with a 95 walk score and easy access to Whole Foods, dozens of restaurants and both Muni and Caltrain, you're likely to never drive your car.

Priced to sell! Nestled in the North Waterfront area, this 6th floor, one bedroom condo with a partial view of the bay, is move in ready! There are new stainless steel appliances in the galley style kitchen, a newly painted interior and an updated bathroom. 1 car parking in building garage. Amenities include a 24 hr front desk security, a remodeled gym, complimentary laundry facilities, a club room with a kitchen and library, and a guest suite that can be reserved for visitors. With a walk score of 90, you're conveniently close to the Bay Club, Financial District, the Waterfront, Embarcadero, Farmers Market and North Beach.

address: 15 Red Rock Way Unit 302N, San Francisco, CA 94131
description: Stunning views of downtown and the bay from big bright windows. This top floor unit features exposed beam ceilings, new carpet, fireplace, and a resort style amenities. Situated in Diamond Heights Village, the property has access to the community pool, hot tub, sauna, walking paths, and recently renovated gym and clubhouse. Easy access to the grocery store and restaurants makes chores a breeze. One car secure parking is included. Photos are virtually staged.

Contemporary, chic, and captivating top floor home with a large and private outdoor space overlooking amazing downtown and San Francisco Bay views located in the dynamic Dogpatch district!
