The upper level has a private bedroom area with an updated bathroom, laundry closet, gorgeous wood floors and a dramatic stairway that leads to the inviting and exclusive outdoor space/patio. There is also deeded parking in this well-maintained building. Do not miss this special home that is close to everything!

Majestic 2BD/2BA loft condo in one of SF's oldest and most historic warehouse buildings. The 'Harbor Lofts' retains its industrial essence with soaring 20' ceilings and rare, exposed brick & timer details. This exceptional corner unit boasts a spacious open floor plan with an updated kitchen complete with a seating stone island & stainless steel appliances. The living room graciously flows to a private, expansive outdoor patio, offering a splendid sense of privacy that is the perfect place to relax, dine al fresco & entertain. Both bedrooms are spacious with en-suite baths and the top level mezzanine office/bonus room overlooks the living room and patio, creating a naturally bright work space or guest bedroom! Complete with an in-unit washer/dryer. This is the ideal melding of modern living with yesteryear's industrial history. Fall in love with a central location close to coffee shops, farmer's market, parks, freeways, transportation & FiDi! Parking included.

address: 2212 Golden Gate Ave, San Francisco, CA 94118
description: A rare opportunity to own a home in San Francisco's Lone Mountain. Only a block from internationally renowned University of San Francisco (USF), this southwest facing property is filled with light and naturally inviting. It sits at a juncture of distinctive neighborhoods: Lone Mountain, Jordan Park, Inner Richmond, and North of the Panhandle (NOPA), with its plethora of fun, culturally diverse restaurants. This home is a short distance from Trader Joe's, the City Center Mall anchored with a Target Store, an Organic Grocery Store, Kaiser Permanente, and Golden Gate Park. Banking is available on Fulton St. and for a caffeine craving, Starbucks is a block away on Masonic. Public records show 1240 sqft for this condominium, 2 Bedrooms and 1.5 Baths. The unit has recessed lights in the kitchen & a bathroom. Updated with 3 new light fixtures, newly painted Interior and just refinished hardwood floors, and a new kitchen faucet. Windows are mostly double paned. W/D in garage. Priced to sell

Quintessential Victorian in the heart of Noe Valley - Just two blocks to Noe's 24th Street restaurants, shops, Philz Coffee, Whole Foods, parks, and transit! Gracious and inviting this full floor flat offers 2 bedrooms, 2 bathrooms, plus an office alcove area. Classic double parlor divides the living room and dining/kitchen. The high ceilings and windows throughout offer an abundance of light and an airy feel. Brazilian teak hardwood floors throughout the main living areas. The updated kitchen offers ample custom cabinetry, stainless steel appliances, both bathrooms have been recently renovated with modern and sleek finishes, both bedrooms are generous in size. One of the bedrooms offers anensuite full bathroom and custom closet. Shared patio area and laundry,1 car designated parking and storage area. HOA has 3 units - 2 units in the front building with a cottage at the rear of the lot.

address: 296 Santa Rosa Ave, San Francisco, CA 94112
listing_broker_name: Better Homes and Gardens Real Estate Thrive
description: Welcome to Mission Terrace! A fabulous, detached, Four-bedroom, One bath home on the border of four desirable neighborhoods: Sunnyside, Bernal Heights, Glen Park, and Excelsior! The classic formal entryway opens to a large open formal living room, a formal dining room with period details, and view windows that showers the home with lots of natural sunlight. There are 3 large bedrooms and a bathroom in the upper level. The largest bedroom even has a private patio! The lower level has a bonus room and lots of potential to expand as your family needs. TWO car garage. Low maintenance backyard. Do not miss this special home that is close to shopping, restaurants, cafes, the newly renovated Balboa park, tennis courts, playground, dog park and skate board park. BART, MUNI, easy access to 101 & 280 freeways, Whole Foods, Canyon Market and Mission Street bodegas.

Amazing top floor 1 bedroom, 1.5 bath loft-style condo just steps from vibrant Fillmore Street. Situated at the sunny southwest corner of the building you will find soaring ceilings with south facing wall of windows, a spacious living area, newly outfitted stainless steel kitchen, and a powder room on the main level. Up one flight is the generous loft bedroom en-suite with full bath and large walk-in closet. Continue up the stairs to your private corner roof deck perched amongst the tree tops providing near 360-degree views. 1 car secured parking. Excellent location to restaurants, shops and services close by makes this property a truly unique offering.

Rare contemporary 3 bed, 3 full bath (or 2 bed + den/office) with PRIVATE ENTRANCE. Townhouse style condo on 2 levels w/private entrance offers home-like feel but w/luxury amenities. Renovated features include Viking appliances, custom Tech Lighting, stone & glass tile throughout, custom closets, luxury custom drapes, partial motorized shades, high ceilings w/floor to ceiling windows, contemporary lighting, hardwood floors, 1 parking space. Across from Oracle Park & oceanfront, private entrance w/patio viewing ballpark allows access from street + great for entertaining friends & family during baseball season or world-famous concerts & events at Oracle Park. Deluxe amenities: 24 hr concierge, valet parking, heated outdoor pool & spa, BBQ & fireplace, sauna, electric charging, entertainment room, business center, conference room, Fitness Center w/views, Brixton Restaurant. Steps from Caltrain, Muni, Safeway, 15 min walk to Ferry Building, BART, Chase Center, easy highway access

Picture-perfect modern pied--terre in Duboce Triangle! Impeccably remodeled 2 bed, 1 bath in quiet 6 unit building just a block from Market & Church. Fresh, chic aesthetic, wonderful light & smart use of space. Open-plan kitchen/living combo w/south-facing bay windows that catch the sun year-round. Gorgeous kitchen remodel w/brand new everything: smokey gray cabinetry, stainless appliances, gas range, glossy subway tile, white quartz counters & huge central dining bar. Wall-to-wall bedroom closets w/Elfa storage & design-savvy mirrored doors that reflect the abundant natural light. Renovated full bath w/soaking tub & shower, lg linen closet & luxe tile work. Lovely new wide-plank hw floors throughout & stacked in-unit w&d. Host a BBQ or pre-dinner drinks on the shared roof deck w/sweeping east, north & west views. Just two blocks to Duboce Park & a quick walk to Lower Haight, Castro, NoPaa sophisticated move-in-ready flat in the heart of city!

This light-filled, top-floor flat offers the ultimate urban paradise. Located where two of San Francisco's most popular neighborhoods meet, at the junction of Noe Valley and Dolores Heights, this 2-bedroom, 1-bath unit features great space, period details and the perfect combination of turn-of-the century charm and modern convenience. Two spacious bedrooms are found at the front of the unit and the generous living room and updated eat-in kitchen are found at the rear of the flat, conveniently located next to the private west-facing balcony. Highlights include wood floors, in-unit laundry located in a nice sunroom off the kitchen, a refreshed full bath and extra storage. This tenancy-in-common unit is part of a charming four-unit 1908 building in a fantastic location near Dolores Park, Noe's bustling 24th Street, cafes, shops and transportation.

Spacious, updated, safe, secure, and ultimately walkable to best of the Mission District. 633 Capp Street bundles everything desirable about living in San Francisco into one complete package. Featuring a tastefully modern kitchen with gorgeous stone countertops & brand new appliances, the open concept kitchen/living offers the best possible arrangement of living space. The fantastic layout provides two large bedrooms and one well-appointed bathroom - all accented by high ceilings, hardwood flooring throughout, and an abundance of natural light. This boutique TIC building also provides a landscaped private getaway backyard space, a recent foundation retrofit, new roof, updated security gates & video doorbell, laundry room, 1 car parking, and a huge private storage room. Just steps from the vibrant Valencia corridor, and walking distance to 24th Street, local restaurants and dining, Dolores Park, BART, MUNI & more, this residence checks all the boxes!

Welcome to Residence #413 at Knox, an industrial-influenced, newly built development on the border of Dogpatch/Potrero. Ideally located within walking distance to the 22nd Caltrain Station & Third Street Muni line, this spacious split two bedroom unit offers beautiful views of a lush garden and plenty of natural light. The residence features a great open floorplan with large windows, quartz counters throughout, upgraded appliances including washer/dryer in unit and NEST air conditioning. Building amenities includes, a Fitness center, BBQ area, Media room, Package room, Bike room, Lobby attendant, & smart intercom entry. Additionally, Knox is considered one of the most sought after buildings in San Francisco, with phenomenal homeowners that will make any newcomer feel completely at home.

Not your everyday downtown condo! Stylish and serene with a rare spacious private patio and peaceful urban vibe! This one is in the BACK of the building, NOT on Bush. Freshly painted with newly refinished hardwood floors. Clean lines showcase the open floor plan. The efficient kitchen with new appliances has counter height seating and is open to the living/dining area. Direct access to a generous private patio. The restful bedroom has outlooks to the patio and courtyard. The high-touch high-service La Galleria HOA amenities include 24/7 lobby attendants/security, professionally landscaped courtyard perfect for socially distant outdoor gatherings or work from home outside. One-car garage parking. On-site laundry (credit card-enabled). Storage space available for rent. Convenience is key and rated with 99 Walkscore®. Easy access to Union Square and the Financial District.

address: 601 Van Ness Ave #31, San Francisco, CA 94102
5175 Diamond Heights Blvd #109, San Francisco, CA 94131
description: Charming Diamond Heights Condo featuring a spacious living room with electric fireplace that overlooks serene courtyard with peek-a-boo views of the San Francisco Bay. Dining area adjacent to an all electric kitchen. Two bedrooms/two bathrooms (one en-suite) with ample closet space, both with access to south facing balcony. Engineered wood flooring throughout the living space and bedrooms. Designated two car tandem parking in garage along with shared washer and dryer provided by the HOA. Located near the Diamond Heights shopping center, Douglass Playground, Upper Douglass Dog Play Area, Glen Park Canyon and multiple MUNI bus lines. Easy access to both Hwy 101 and I-280.

Dramatic and flexible 1 Bedroom + Den, 2 full Bathroom floorplan and an abundance of South Facing, natural light combine to create a sophisticated urban home located in burgeoning central SOMA. Spacious enough to social distance, this meticulously maintained live/work loft comes replete with numerous modern amenities including gleaming hardwood floors, multiple skylights, chef's kitchen with SS appliances, gas range, gas fireplace and a walk-in closet. The flexible Den space can cross function as home office, Zoom Room or guest sleeping area. Additional recent upgrades include freshly painted cabinets, newly installed window treatments and designer lighting package throughout. In-unit W/D, HUGE onsite storage, 1 car full size garage parking space and low HOA dues complete the package for this ultimate City abode. Convenient SOMA location with easy access to countless neighborhood amenities and eateries, 280/101, Embarcadero waterfront and San Francisco's sunniest micro climate.

address: 151 Alice B. Toklas Pl #601, San Francisco, CA 94109
description: Rarely available beautiful contemporary loft condo in the iconic Marquee Loft Building located in the heart of San Francisco! The open floor plan features a living /dining area and a gourmet kitchen with stainless appliances and a center island. There also is a private bedroom with closet organizer, spacious bath, wood floors, exposed beams, laundry hookup in the unit, large storage across the hall, and one-car parking. A very nice special urban home at a great price!

Have it all with this absolute dream home in the heart of Bernal Heights! 8 Montezuma is a one-of-a-kind condo that offers 2BD, 1BA, a private parking garage, an exclusive lush yard + patio, storage, laundry, and of course... views! The 2 spacious bedrooms enjoy captivating outlooks from the classic bay windows of the dazzling city skyline and Twin Peaks. The inviting entertaining area enjoys marvelous afternoon light and opens up to a magical alfresco escape where a deeded garden terrace boasts golden sunsets. This sun-kissed garden and patio space is the perfect place for a zoom call, barbecue party, or just simply to enjoy the birdsong and butterflies. Back inside, the efficient kitchen is outfitted with an eat-in area, garden views, and stainless steel appliances including a new gas stove and dishwasher. Live the Bernal lifestyle, close to the best of SF restaurants & cafes, numerous parks, freeways and transportation.

Relish an elevated level of living in this top-floor 2 bed / 1 bath home in NOPA with modern convenience and 1920's charm. Enjoy it all: chef's kitchen, formal dining room, in-unit laundry, storage room and 1-car parking. Enter up the stairwell into the landing that graciously opens into the window-lined, tranquil living room; this is the heart of your home. A bespoke arched ceiling invites you into the spacious dining room. Your gourmet kitchen has all the right ingredients to cook with ease: stainless steel appliances, ample countertops, cabinetry and an impeccable Bertazzoni stove with vented hood. Transitioning into the hallway is your generously-sized bathroom with rain shower and marble surround. Your two bedrooms feature designer detail, full closets, and natural light from their oversized windows. The building's expansive, landscaped backyard is truly an impressive oasis. Just steps to the Panhandle and amazing shops, cafes and in-demand eateries. Don't miss!

address: 5150 Diamond Heights Blvd Unit 307B, SAN FRANCISCO, CA 94131
description: The best of urban living in this top floor corner unit at the desirable Diamond Heights Village. Serene, calming view of the natural landscape through large living room window. Smaller side window dazzles with view of the Bay. This spacious and charming home features a walk-in closet in the bedroom, an abundance of natural light, gas fireplace, gas stove, large bathroom, new paint and plenty of storage. Laundry room on first floor. Complex features an abundance of welcoming and soothing retreat-like outdoor space lush greenery and mature trees along walkways, benches, pond, cascading water and walking bridges. HOA amenities simplify the city lifestyle with an out-door heated pool, spa, sauna, private shower/changing area, fitness center with newer equipment, updated clubhouse with lounging area, billiards, TV and free WiFi. Deeded parking space in secured garage with on-site EV charging stations. Conveniently located near two dog parks, Glen Canyon Park and DH Shopping Center.

description: New Year, new price! Show and sell! Thrive in Lake Merced Hill Community where clean air is provided by the towering trees and the environment is peaceful and relaxing. The Wellness center with a swimming pool, 3 tennis courts, spa and sauna! Walk around the Lake Merced and close to 4 golf courses. Commutes are eased with the proximity to the freeways. Beautifully remodeled spacious condo, nice entry foyer, lrg.living room with mirrored built-in shelves on either side of the frp. Lrg. dining area open to a light filled den/off. Eat-in, chef's delight, european style kitchen with Bosch dishwasher and oven and W/D combo, granite island/table. Lrg. Master br, huge walk-in, built out closet. lrg. remod. m/ba, radiant heat floor. Good size 2nd br, remod 2nd bath, both BA have radiant heat floor. Full size park space in the garage, elevator from gar. Extra parking spaces on first come basis. 24 hr security.

Just steps from the best shops & restaurants on Clement street lies a wonderful reprieve from the bustle of city living. The elegant living room with wood-burning fireplace flows into the dining room & kitchen. Cooking is a pleasure in the remodeled kitchen, equipped w/under-cabinet lighting, a dual-fuel 40'' range, honed granite counters & Bosch DW. Across the back of the home are two spacious off-street bedrooms. The bathroom offers a separate tub & stall shower and is adorned with a beveled-glass door. Additional features include louvered shutters, window blinds, hardwood floors, a coat closet, and linen closet. One-car independent parking, abundant shared storage, and a stacked washer/dryer are located on the ground floor. When you're not venturing off to nearby Mountain Lake Park, Golden Gate Park or the Presidio, enjoy some down-time having a meal or relaxing in the sun on the shared rear patio. Enjoy the convenience & comfort of this centrally-located Inner Richmond condo!

Located in the heart of the Marina, but not on liquefaction, this fantastic two bedroom, two bathroom flat is steps away from Fort Mason, Moscone Park and the many boutique shops and restaurants of Chestnut and Union St. Located in a charming 1920's building with elegant detailing and a beautiful lobby, the home features custom built-ins, remodeled kitchen and bathrooms, ensuite primary bedroom, hardwood floors, ample closet space, in-unit washer and dryer, parking and tons of storage. The unit is located in the back of the building and is both quiet and serene, as it overlooks the shared garden. The building also has a shared rooftop deck with an incredible view of the Golden Gate Bridge, Palace of Fine Arts, and city landscape.

address: 875 La Playa St #181, San Francisco, CA 94121
description: Rare corner residence with unobstructed ocean & Golden Gate Park views at pristine location by the beach. Open, spacious & light abundant floor plan. Bright and airy kitchen with breakfast bar opens to generously sized dining/living room combo. Features include two private balconies, wood floors throughout the home, in-unit laundry, and abundant closet space. 1 car parking and exclusive use storage cage in the garage. Building amenities include elevator, a gorgeous central courtyard with BBQ grills and seating, bicycle storage room, fitness center, & more. Steps from the beach, Golden Gate Park, Land's End, and Cliff House. Welcome home to your new beach retreat!

address: 1186 Eddy St Unit B, San Francisco, CA 94109
description: Live the San Francisco life in a picturesque Cathedral Hill location just across from Jefferson Square Park! If you are looking for a bright, modern two bedroom, two bath condo with low HOA dues this home is for you. It's freshly painted throughout with an open concept living & dining room area including an updated kitchen that boasts lovely granite countertops and stainless steel appliances. The home includes a front patio area, intercom system, plus free in-building laundry, and there is shared rooftop terrace for those relaxing moments. You will be living in a gated property that comes complete with a generously sized designated parking spot and storage space inside a secured garage. This property is also in close proximity to Japantown, Fillmore District, Civic Center, Hayes Valley, and the new CPMC Campus. Virtual tour https://my.matterport.com/show/?m=mjBvEsg2ta6

Make the Presidio your playground in this breathtaking 1BD/1BA garden TIC that opens to a shared yard on desirable Lake Street. This spacious and bright home is the perfect city sanctuary. The spacious living room/dining area has serene garden views. The open kitchen features abundant cabinetry, granite counters and Frigidaire stainless steel appliances. Enjoy meals in the windowed dining area, or step outside to the exclusive use area or the oversized shared yard for al fresco dining and entertaining. The bedroom offers space for a sitting or office area, and the bathroom includes a tub/shower and a roomy vanity topped in stone. Three good size closets, and a laundry closet with a stacked washer-dryer add comfort and convenience to this spectacular home. Gorgeous Lake Street is currently under consideration to become a Permanent Slow Street, adding tremendous appeal to this serene park-side neighborhood.

205 Carl St was renovated 'down to the studs' w/ seismic upgrades (steel moment frame, foundation upgraded visible in garage). This 2-level unit features 3 spacious BRs, 2.5 BAs, 1 car SbyS parking and storage. The main level consists of an open floor plan, granite, stainless, gas kitchen, 2 BR and 1.5 BA. The lower lvl features a beautiful master suite with a gorgeous BA and spacious closet. Beautiful HW floors. Leased Tesla Solar system - see disclosures for details. Just outside the master is a unique garden seating area with incredible ambience, exclusive use. The other areas of the yard are common. Walk to tech stops/MUNI. Cole Valley is a distinct neighborhood with shopping, GG Park, major hospitals and other conveniences just steps away.

This bright, elegant top floor 2 bedroom Pacific Heights condo captures the beauty of the turn of the century with contemporary conveniences. And you can even visit with friends when you take the elevator up to dine al fresco on a roof deck full of fresh air and spectacular views.

Wonderful Outer Sunset home perfect for first time buyers and those wishing to put their personal stamp on this lovely home. Possible potential for easy expansion. Transparent pricing. Below Market Rate (BMR) housing opportunity available at 100% Area Median Income (AMI). Maximum income for 1 person = 86,200, 2 people = $98,500; 3 = $106,550; 4 = $110,850, etc. Must be 1st-time homebuyer & income eligible. Unit available thru the Mayor's Office of Housing and Community Development (MOHCD) & subject to resale controls, monitoring & other restrictions. Unit will be listed on DAHLIA, the SF Housing Portal (https://housing.sfgov.org) Applications will be received on a First Come, First Served basis. Visit https://sfmohcd.org/BMR-Resale-855-Folsom-Unit-941 for application & program info. Fair Housing Opportunity

3 beds, 2.5 baths and family room. All rooms in ground floor built w/permit. Hardwood floor w/crown molding, dual pane windows. Large backyard w/a patio and garden. Unique opportunities await in this vacant 2 unit property, ideal for a developer or owner user, ready for thoughtful restoration or personalization. The exterior staircase has been updated and a new roof was done in 2003. Period details, traditional 10' ceilings, and a wider profile for larger rooms than one might expect. Close to shopping, freeway access, private schools, and SF General.
